# ResumeLens Project Overview

## What is ResumeLens?
A full-stack Next.js application that analyzes resumes against target engineering roles using AI.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16+ (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (primary styling)
- Zod (validation)
- React hooks (state management)

## Key Directories
- `src/app/` - Pages and API routes
- `src/features/` - Feature modules (resume-upload, resume-analysis, etc.)
- `src/components/ui/` - Domain-agnostic UI primitives
- `src/components/layout/` - App layout components
- `src/server/` - Server-only code (AI, parsing)
- `src/lib/` - Shared utilities, schemas, constants
- `src/types/` - TypeScript type definitions

## MVP Scope
- Upload PDF, DOCX, TXT resumes
- Select target role (Frontend, React, Angular, Full Stack)
- AI parses and analyzes resume
- Display structured feedback with rewrites

## Out of Scope
- Authentication
- Database
- File storage
- OCR
